org.eclipse.viatra.transformation.views.traceability.patterns

Class Helpers

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.impl.BaseQueryGroup
      • org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.impl.BaseGeneratedPatternGroup
        • org.eclipse.viatra.transformation.views.traceability.patterns.Helpers
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IQueryGroup

    public final class Helpers
extends BaseGeneratedPatternGroup
    A pattern group formed of all public patterns defined in helpers.vql.

    Use the static instance as any org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.IPatternGroup, to conveniently prepare a VIATRA Query engine for matching all patterns originally defined in file helpers.vql, in order to achieve better performance than one-by-one on-demand matcher initialization.

    From package org.eclipse.viatra.transformation.views.traceability.patterns, the group contains the definition of the following patterns:

    • emptyTrace
    • trace2target
    • trace2param
    • trace2object
    • param2target
    • trace
    See Also:
    IPatternGroup
